      formIIA: "“This fossil shows fine detail in the ridges and segments, which tells me it was buried quickly — if it had decomposed slowly in the open, none of that detail would have survived. That tells me the burial event itself, whatever it was, must have happened suddenly rather than gradually.”",
      journal: "A detailed fossil drawing with the 'to become a fossil, it would have needed to...' sentence completed; Age 11 adds a full paragraph on the burial conditions required.",
